<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:03:37 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>针对肝纤维化中肝细胞介导的串扰的药理学策略</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/pharmacological-strategies-targeting-hepatocyte-mediated-crosstalk-in-liver-fibrosis</link><description>肝纤维化是慢性肝损伤的常见病理结果。由于肝纤维化的发病机制复杂，许多治疗药物表现出有限的临床疗效或显着的副作用。这一挑战强调了确定潜在治疗靶点并改进现有疗法的迫切需要。肝细胞是肝纤维化的关键启动子，积极参与与其他肝细胞类型的信号串扰，以促进纤维形成。对以肝细胞为中心的信号串扰的理解的进展使得能够识别潜在的治疗靶点。此外，调节多种途径的联合疗法和改善药理学特性的药物修饰可能有助于最大限度地减少副作用并增强现有治疗的疗效。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pharmacological-strategies-targeting-hepatocyte-mediated-crosstalk-in-liver-fibrosis.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:03:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/pharmacological-strategies-targeting-hepatocyte-mediated-crosstalk-in-liver-fibrosis</guid></item><item><title>STMN2/β-丙氨酸控制的代谢重编程调节小细胞肺癌的神经元侵袭</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/regulation-of-neuronal-invasion-of-small-cell-lung-cancer-by-stmn2-%ce%b2-alanine-controlled-metabolic-reprogramming</link><description>周等人。证明神经周围浸润（PNI）是小细胞肺癌的不良预后因素。他们确定了神经元-STMN2-β-丙氨酸轴，其中神经微环境上调肿瘤细胞中的STMN2，重新编程β-丙氨酸代谢以增强细胞迁移并驱动神经侵袭，揭示了潜在的治疗靶点。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/regulation-of-neuronal-invasion-of-small-cell-lung-cancer-by-stmn2-ceb2-alanine-controlled-metabolic-reprogramming.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 13:48:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/regulation-of-neuronal-invasion-of-small-cell-lung-cancer-by-stmn2-%ce%b2-alanine-controlled-metabolic-reprogramming</guid></item><item><title>髓磷脂可塑性中神经递质激活的 GPCR 信号传导</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/neurotransmitter-activated-gpcr-signaling-in-myelin-plasticity</link><description>髓鞘形成越来越被认为是一个动态的、适应性的过程，在整个生命过程中受到少突胶质细胞的调节。除了提供电绝缘之外，髓磷脂还支持轴突代谢，并可以在代谢应激下充当能量库，凸显了生理髓磷脂周转的重要性。髓鞘动力学失调会导致多种神经系统疾病，包括脱髓鞘、神经退行性和神经精神疾病。越来越多的证据表明，通过少突胶质细胞系细胞表达的 G 蛋白偶联受体 (GPCR) 发出的神经递质信号传导可调节髓磷脂的形成、重塑和修复。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neurotransmitter-activated-gpcr-signaling-in-myelin-plasticity2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 13:33:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/neurotransmitter-activated-gpcr-signaling-in-myelin-plasticity</guid></item><item><title>与偏头痛相关的紧急医疗保健遭遇的急性环境触发因素和中期调节因素</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/acute-environmental-triggers-and-intermediate-term-modulators-of-emergency-migraine-related-health-care-encounters</link><description>该网站使用安全服务来防范恶意机器人。当网站验证您不是机器人时会显示此页面。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/acute-environmental-triggers-and-intermediate-term-modulators-of-emergency-migraine-related-health-care-encounters2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 13:18:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/acute-environmental-triggers-and-intermediate-term-modulators-of-emergency-migraine-related-health-care-encounters</guid></item><item><title>肠道微生物群衍生的脱氧胆酸塑造免疫抑制肿瘤微环境并促进乳腺癌进展</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gut-microbiota-derived-deoxycholic-acid-shapes-an-immunosuppressive-tumor-microenvironment-and-promotes-breast-cancer-progression</link><description>李等人。确定脱氧胆酸是乳腺癌进展的微生物群衍生驱动因素。脱氧胆酸激活法尼醇 X 受体信号传导，诱导白细胞介素 6 产生，促进免疫抑制细胞募集并建立具有治疗潜力的代谢物驱动的免疫调节轴。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/gut-microbiota-derived-deoxycholic-acid-shapes-an-immunosuppressive-tumor-microenvironment-and-promotes-breast-cancer-progression2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 13:03:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gut-microbiota-derived-deoxycholic-acid-shapes-an-immunosuppressive-tumor-microenvironment-and-promotes-breast-cancer-progression</guid></item><item><title>来自 X 射线脉冲的更清晰的信号</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/cleaner-signals-from-x-ray-pulses</link><description>经过改进的光学技术通过消除背景光揭示了超快 X 射线脉冲的时间结构。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cleaner-signals-from-x-ray-pulses.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 12:48:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/cleaner-signals-from-x-ray-pulses</guid></item><item><title>液晶提供按需斯格明子</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/liquid-crystals-offer-on-demand-skyrmions</link><description>一种在液晶中创建扭曲结构的新方法可能有助于控制它们以实现可能的内存存储应用。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/liquid-crystals-offer-on-demand-skyrmions.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 12:33:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/liquid-crystals-offer-on-demand-skyrmions</guid></item><item><title>更亮的红色 micro-LED 有助于解决全彩显示稳定性挑战</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brighter-red-micro-leds-could-help-solve-full-color-display-stability-challenge</link><description>大阪大学的研究人员与立命馆大学合作，证明在半极性晶面上生长掺铕氮化镓（Eu 掺杂 GaN）可显着改善红光发射。研究小组发现，这种方法选择性地促进高效Eu发光中心的形成，导致红光发射强度比传统生长的极面材料高3.6倍以上。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brighter-red-micro-leds-could-help-solve-full-color-display-stability-challenge.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 12:18:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brighter-red-micro-leds-could-help-solve-full-color-display-stability-challenge</guid></item><item><title>黑洞碰撞产生的引力波可能有助于探测暗物质</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gravitational-waves-from-colliding-black-holes-may-allow-detection-of-dark-matter</link><description>暗物质被认为构成了宇宙中的大部分物质，但它与周围环境相互作用的唯一方式是通过重力。如果两个碰撞的黑洞螺旋穿过暗物质密集区域并合并，那么跨越空间和时间的引力波可能会带有暗物质的印记。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/gravitational-waves-from-colliding-black-holes-may-allow-detection-of-dark-matter.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 12:03:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gravitational-waves-from-colliding-black-holes-may-allow-detection-of-dark-matter</guid></item><item><title>引力波探测器现在可以“自动调谐”信号以协调天空</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gravitational-wave-detectors-can-now-autotune-signals-to-harmonize-the-heavens</link><description>研究世界上最灵敏的科学仪器的引力波研究人员已经找到了一种使用类似于音乐制作中使用的音调校正的过程来调整探测器的方法。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/gravitational-wave-detectors-can-now-autotune-signals-to-harmonize-the-heavens3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 11:48:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gravitational-wave-detectors-can-now-autotune-signals-to-harmonize-the-heavens</guid></item></channel></rss>